            <p align="justify">13. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A corpus fund of &#x20B9; 25 lac & &#x20B9; 12.5 lac has been created for officers & JCO/OR respectively for special category of handicapped Army personnel who are invalided out of service with 100 percent disability and are provided Constant Attendant Allowance permanently for diseases/conditions of total blindness, paraplegia, quadriplegia, irreversible comatose condition due to irreversible Brain damage as a result of trauma, infection, stroke or any cause leading to permanent vegetative state or equivalent, persons loosing two limbs i.e. Amputation of both legs (Above Knee) and both Arms (Above Elbow) and are dependant on others for their day to day activities and survival. This will be in addition to the normal disability benefit. The corpus fund will be invested by Army Group Insurance Fund in a fixed deposit of a Nationalised Bank and the interest earnings will be given to the beneficiary during his life period only. This will cease on his demise and the corpus fund will revert to Army Group Insurance Fund.</p>
